  "description": "<i>Triada</i> is a compilation of the three following titles:<ul>\n<li><i>Ashido</i> is a puzzle solving game, where the player must place stones with symbols in an appropriate manner on the board. \nLaying stones correspond to the appropriate rules. The game features 70 levels, all with individual password. </li>\n<li><i>Bombi</i> is a side scrolling clone of <a href=\"https://www.mobygames.com/game/bomberman\">Dyna Blaster</a> or <a href=\"https://www.mobygames.com/search/quick?game=Bomberman\">Bomberman</a> for two players. The goal is to eliminate the opponent by detonating an explosive when an enemy is in its range. Getting close to the opposite player requires avoiding various creatures and removing walls and other obstacles inside the maze. Some of the destroyed parts of the maze may hide very useful power-ups, such as additional bombs or extra protectors.</li>\n<li><i>Timtris</i> is a clone of classic <a href=\"https://www.mobygames.com/search/quick?game=Tetris\">Tetris</a>. The player gets a point for each completed line. The game finishes when the blocks cease to be housed in the well.</li>\n</ul>",
